eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 60 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
No abdominal fistula, gastrointestinal perforation, or intra-abdominal abscess within the past 28 days

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Number of days from the date the subject is randomized to the date the subject experiences a confirmed event of disease progression or to the date of death if disease progression is not reached
outcome_measures.time_frame: Measured up to 5 years after the last subject has enrolled in the study.

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will explore whether knowledge-based planning (KBP) can improve IG-IMRT plans compared to plans that would have been delivered without KBP, estimate the resulting toxicity reduction using normal tissue complication probability (NTCP) models, and determine whether KBP should be a requirement for future IG-IMRT protocols
outcome_measures.measure: Type of intensity modulated radiation therapy (IG-IMRT)
